Colour
: Live specimen golden-olive (
Hickin 1954
), pale ventrally. Specimens preserved in ethanol reddish brown, dorsum dark, ventrally pale; on abdomen, semicircular-triangular pale anterior dorsolateral areas, dorsocentral area of segments with darker circular pale spots, connected caudally with anterior dorsolateral areas through pale lines, forming W-shape. Sclerotized areas of head and thorax dark brown with pale areas, black in some places (
Fig 22a
).

